{
  "metadata": {
    "anchor_id": "member_e",
    "description": "29-year-old female, PPO plan. COBRA/life event arc — pregnancy, job loss, COBRA gap and retroactive election, new employer coverage, delivery, dependent add. Jan–Nov 2025 longitudinal narrative.",
    "created": "2026-03-06",
    "narrative_summary": "Ashley Rivera is a 29-year-old first-time mother in Los Angeles on a PPO plan. She confirmed her pregnancy in January 2025 and began routine prenatal care with her OB/GYN. In April she was laid off from Meridian Healthcare Systems and lost her Gold PPO coverage effective April 30. She initially did not elect COBRA, thinking she would find new insurance quickly. At her 20-week anatomy scan in May, she realized she was uninsured. She retroactively elected COBRA within the 60-day window, restoring coverage effective May 1. However, she could only afford two months of COBRA premiums ($663/month), so COBRA lapsed after June 30. Her 28-week prenatal visit on July 15 was denied — no active coverage. In August she started a new job at Pinnacle Financial Group with a Silver PPO plan. She delivered a healthy baby girl in October via normal vaginal delivery with a 2-night hospital stay. In November she called to add the baby as a dependent on her new plan."
  },

