      "sentiment": "Anxious",
      "notes": "Member called urgently about health insurance coverage gap. Was laid off from Meridian Healthcare Systems on 4/30 and did not initially elect COBRA. Now 20 weeks pregnant with upcoming anatomy scan and realized she has no coverage. Very anxious. Walked member through COBRA election process — still within 60-day window. Explained retroactive coverage, premium costs ($663/month), and payment timeline. Member elected COBRA on the call. Confirmed prenatal claims from May forward will be covered. Member expressed concern about COBRA cost ($663/month) — stated she can probably afford 2 months while job searching. Advised that COBRA will lapse if premiums not paid and any claims after lapse would be denied. Member understood the risk. Long call due to detailed COBRA explanation and payment setup.",
